  nagorno - karabakh is internationally recognized as part of azerbaijan , but most of the region is governed by the nagorno - karabakh republic , a de facto independent but unrecognized state established on the basis of the nagorno - karabakh autonomous oblast of the azerbaijan ssr. azerbaijan has not exercised political authority over the region since the advent of the karabakh movement in 1988 .

